Job Description:  AiQoD is seeking a diligent and detail-oriented Data Entry Operator to join our team. The ideal  candidate will be responsible for accurate and efficient entry of various data types, including but  not limited to invoice entry, solution drawing, and other IT and NON IT-related entries. Strong  English communication skills are essential for effective collaboration within the team and with  clients.   Responsibilities:   1. Perform data entry tasks with high accuracy and efficiency.  2. Inputting invoices and ensuring all necessary information is recorded correctly.  3. Create solution drawings entry based on provided specifications or instructions.  4. Maintain data integrity and confidentiality at all times.  5. Assist in other IT and NON-IT-related data entry tasks as assigned.  6. Communicate effectively with team members and clients to clarify requirements or  resolve discrepancies.  7. Identify and report any errors or inconsistencies in the data.    Requirements:   1. Proven experience as a Data Entry Operator or similar role.(Fresher are welcome)  2. 0-1 Years of Experience Required.  3. Strong proficiency in English language, both written and verbal, is essential.  4. Excellent typing skills and attention to detail.  5. Proficiency in using data entry software and tools (e.g. MS Office is must, annotation  tool is a must.)  6. Ability to work efficiently under tight deadlines.  7. Strong problem-solving skills and ability to adapt to changes.  8. Prior experience with invoice entry, IT and NON IT-related data entry is a plus.  9. Knowledge of basic computer applications and familiarity with relevant software  programs. 10. Ability to maintain confidentiality and handle sensitive information securely.    Preferred Qualifications:   1. Associate's or Bachelor's degree in a related field.  2. Certification in data entry or relevant training programs.  3. Familiarity with basic IT concepts and terminology.   Join our dynamic team at AiQoD and contribute to our mission of leveraging artificial  intelligence for quality data management. column1: Executive - Machine Operator( Male candidates only)
column2: Roles and Responsibilities     Job   Description :   Operators are expected to know & follow the processes in place. Other than the general processes, the job specific processes are also to be followed by the operators. Operators are supposed to produce the cards as per the schedule/instructions given by the Supervisor. While loading the new job, operators should check the data, plastics, mailers, foils etc. Operators should fill up the Indents / Job cards / registers completely without any mistakes.  At the end of the shift, operators should hand over the produced cards, damaged cards, balance plastics, Indents, Check Lists and other documents to the next shift operators. In case Job is completed during the shift, all the documents should be filed properly in the respective files. The cards should be handled with ut-most care. Not a single card should be misplaced. Once the indent is completed, the cards should be tallied properly. No files and cards should be remaining except the hold cases. 1st level QC should be done by the operators i.e. visual checks for various points like photo, signature, embossing, tipping/magstripe/CHIP etc. Each and every card should be checked for quality to ensure 100 % accuracy.

column2: * Barclays is an international financial services provider engaged in personal banking,  credit cards,  corporate and investment banking and wealth management with an extensive presence in Europe,  the Americas ,  Africa and Asia . Barclays purpose is to help people achieve their ambitions in the right way. With over 300 years of history and expertise in banking,  Barclays operates in over 50 countries and employs approximately 140, 000 people. Barclays moves,  lends,  invests and protects money for customers and clients worldwide.  At Barclays,  we recruit based on merit and are committed to promoting diversity throughout our organisation.  About the Team  Barclays moves,  lends,  invests and protects money for customers and clients worldwide . Please visit our website here for more information  Overall purpose of role:  To be the primary point of contact for Barclays customers,  delivering a high- quality effective telephone/ online banking service  Main Duties and Responsibilities  Key Accountabilities and Skills required:  Key specific accountabilities.  Handle customer requests with the support of clearly defined scripts and processes  Adhere to the Service Level Agreements specified by the client /  process  Ensure adherence to time schedules  May have the authority to release and verify funds across a variety of systems used by the department  Stakeholder management and leadership.  Deal with customers and may be required to identify,  log and escalate complaints and resolve queries by tracking them internally and escalate upwards if necessary  Responsible for the management of own daily workload,  to ensure telephone enquiries /  queries are dealt with in an efficient and knowledgeable manner to meet the demands of the business grades of service  Ensuring that all unresolved cases /  queries are allocated to the respective areas  Responsible for identifying potential loss situations promptly escalating to the relevant areas to minimise the risk to the business and the customer  Decision making and problem solving.  Adhere to organizational wide information security policies and procedures  Assist Team Manager /  Process Expert in administration of the section,  including organising workflow,  queue management and query resolution  Understand customer s queries and identify suitable solutions using probing questioning and problem solving techniques.  To accurately and efficiently administer all relevant paperwork and post call wrap up .  To react to & progress sales opportunities related to customer needs,  where applicable  Risk and Control: All Barclays colleagues have to ensure that all activities and duties are carried out in full compliance with regulatory requirements,  Enterprise Wide Risk Management Framework and internal Barclays Policies and Policy Standards  Requirements  Your Skills and Qualifications will include  Skills  Effective communication,  including questioning skills  Active listening skills  Minimum B2 12 English Language Fluency (CEF)  High customer focus and ability to address customer needs effectively  Ability to work in shifts  Skilled in generating sales leads and cross sales opportunities and selling a defined range of Bank products,  where applicable  MS Office Applications (preferably,  Excel,  word & PowerPoint)  Education & Experience  Essential  o relevant experience  o Under- Graduate/ Graduate/ Post- Graduate in any discipline (Fresher s applicable however preferably Graduate Fresher)  o Experience of working in a customer facing service environment  o Flexibility in hours of work and ability to work changing shifts patterns  Preferred  o Experience of working in a Sales environment  o Experience of working in BPO/ KPO  o Familiarity with procedures,  policies,  products and services of a financial organisation  o Ability to work within deadlines/ customer demand  The Benefits: Our customers deserve the best. The same goes for our employees. That's why at Barclays you'll receive a range of benefits that include a competitive salary and all the tools,  technology and support you need to succeed.  Our Culture: Everything we do is shaped by the five values of Respect,  Integrity,  Service,  Excellence and Stewardship. The values inform the foundations of our relationships with customers and clients,  but they also shape how we measure and reward the performance of our employees. Simply put,  success is not just about what you achieve,  but about how you achieve it.  Dynamic working gives everyone at Barclays the opportunity to integrate professional and personal lives,  if you have a need for flexibility then please discuss this with the hiring manager.  Barclays is an equal opportunity employer and are opposed to discrimination on any grounds. For more detailed information,  please visit our dedicated Diversity and Inclusion site here .  Barclays Values and Diversity  Our common purpose is to help people achieve their ambitions in the right way. We ll measure and reward our people,  not just on commercial results,  but on how they live our Values of Respect,  Integrity,  Service,  Excellence and Stewardship and bring them to life every day. To find out more about working at Barclays and the development opportunities we offer please visit our website www.barclays.com  We are an equal opportunity employer and we are opposed to discrimination on any grounds. column2: Role & responsibilities   A Staffing Coordinator is an administrative employee who handles routine clerical tasks relating to entering or updating data in a computer system. Some additional responsibilities may include: Collecting data and inputting information into databases Sorting and Formatting MS word documents in the desired format required to be entered to database. Reviewing records for accuracy Updating databases with new or revised information as necessary Performing regular backups of information to ensure data preservation Retrieving records and electronic files from the database Sorting and organizing paper records or notes after data entry Preparing digital materials or files for printing Providing team members with requested data or information Performing comparative analyses of different data sources for administrative purposes     Preferred candidate profile   Staffing Coordinators require high-level quality control and accuracy to ensure all data remains valid and correct. Since they work with important data for organizations, they may test data to ensure it meets the standards of the organization. This means they provide accurate data to the organizations, which the organization then uses to make decisions. column2: Data Entry: The primary responsibility of a data entry operator is to input data accurately and efficiently into computer systems. This involves typing, scanning, and entering various types of information, such as customer details, financial records, inventory data, and other relevant data.      Database Management: Data entry operators often work with databases to store and retrieve information. They may be responsible for creating and maintaining databases, updating existing records, and ensuring data integrity and accuracy.      Data Verification: Data entry operators are responsible for verifying the accuracy of entered data. They may cross-check information against source documents, proofread entries, and make necessary corrections or edits as required.      Quality Control: Ensuring data quality and consistency is essential. Data entry operators may perform quality control checks to identify errors, inconsistencies, or missing information. They may also collaborate with team members or supervisors to resolve any data-related issues.      Data Maintenance: Data entry operators may be involved in organizing and managing data files and records. They may ensure files are labeled and stored appropriately, create backups, and maintain security and confidentiality of sensitive data.      Research and Documentation: In some cases, data entry operators may be required to conduct research to gather additional information or verify data accuracy. They may also assist in preparing reports, presentations, or other documentation based on the entered data.      Communication and Collaboration: Data entry operators may work closely with other team members, supervisors, or clients to clarify data requirements, address queries, or coordinate on specific projects. Effective communication and collaboration skills are important in this role.      Efficiency and Speed: Data entry operators are expected to perform their tasks efficiently and with a high level of accuracy. They may need to meet specific productivity targets or deadlines while maintaining data quality standards.      Technical Skills: Proficiency in using computer systems, data entry software, and relevant tools is crucial. Data entry operators should be comfortable with typing, data entry software, spreadsheet applications, and basic computer operations.      Attention to Detail: Paying close attention to detail is essential to minimize errors and maintain data accuracy. Data entry operators should have good proofreading skills and the ability to spot inconsistencies or mistakes in the entered data.

column2: * Barclays is an international financial services provider engaged in personal banking,  credit cards,  corporate and investment banking and wealth management with an extensive presence in Europe,  the Americas ,  Africa and Asia . Barclays purpose is to help people achieve their ambitions in the right way. With over 300 years of history and expertise in banking,  Barclays operates in over 50 countries and employs approximately 140, 000 people. Barclays moves,  lends,  invests and protects money for customers and clients worldwide.  At Barclays,  we recruit based on merit and are committed to promoting diversity throughout our organisation.  About the Team  Barclays moves,  lends,  invests and protects money for customers and clients worldwide . Please visit our website here for more information  Overall purpose of role:  To be the primary point of contact for Barclays customers,  delivering a high- quality effective telephone/ online banking service  Main Duties and Responsibilities  Key Accountabilities and Skills required:  Key specific accountabilities.  Handle customer requests with the support of clearly defined scripts and processes  Adhere to the Service Level Agreements specified by the client /  process  Ensure adherence to time schedules  May have the authority to release and verify funds across a variety of systems used by the department  Stakeholder management and leadership.  Deal with customers and may be required to identify,  log and escalate complaints and resolve queries by tracking them internally and escalate upwards if necessary  Responsible for the management of own daily workload,  to ensure telephone enquiries /  queries are dealt with in an efficient and knowledgeable manner to meet the demands of the business grades of service  Ensuring that all unresolved cases /  queries are allocated to the respective areas  Responsible for identifying potential loss situations promptly escalating to the relevant areas to minimise the risk to the business and the customer  Decision making and problem solving.  Adhere to organizational wide information security policies and procedures  Assist Team Manager /  Process Expert in administration of the section,  including organising workflow,  queue management and query resolution  Understand customer s queries and identify suitable solutions using probing questioning and problem solving techniques.  To accurately and efficiently administer all relevant paperwork and post call wrap up .  To react to & progress sales opportunities related to customer needs,  where applicable  Risk and Control: All Barclays colleagues have to ensure that all activities and duties are carried out in full compliance with regulatory requirements,  Enterprise Wide Risk Management Framework and internal Barclays Policies and Policy Standards  Requirements  Your Skills and Qualifications will include  Skills  Effective communication,  including questioning skills  Active listening skills  Minimum B2 12 English Language Fluency (CEF)  High customer focus and ability to address customer needs effectively  Ability to work in shifts  Skilled in generating sales leads and cross sales opportunities and selling a defined range of Bank products,  where applicable  MS Office Applications (preferably,  Excel,  word & PowerPoint)  Education & Experience  Essential  o relevant experience  o Under- Graduate/ Graduate/ Post- Graduate in any discipline (Fresher s applicable however preferably Graduate Fresher)  o Experience of working in a customer facing service environment  o Flexibility in hours of work and ability to work changing shifts patterns  Preferred  o Experience of working in a Sales environment  o Experience of working in BPO/ KPO  o Familiarity with procedures,  policies,  products and services of a financial organisation  o Ability to work within deadlines/ customer demand  The Benefits: Our customers deserve the best. The same goes for our employees. That's why at Barclays you'll receive a range of benefits that include a competitive salary and all the tools,  technology and support you need to succeed.  Our Culture: Everything we do is shaped by the five values of Respect,  Integrity,  Service,  Excellence and Stewardship. The values inform the foundations of our relationships with customers and clients,  but they also shape how we measure and reward the performance of our employees. Simply put,  success is not just about what you achieve,  but about how you achieve it.  Dynamic working gives everyone at Barclays the opportunity to integrate professional and personal lives,  if you have a need for flexibility then please discuss this with the hiring manager.  Barclays is an equal opportunity employer and are opposed to discrimination on any grounds. For more detailed information,  please visit our dedicated Diversity and Inclusion site here . column2: We are currently looking for a diligent and meticulous Data Entry Operator to become part of our dynamic team in Bhiwadi. In this role, you will play a critical part in managing and maintaining our extensive databases. Your focus will be on the accurate and timely entry of various types of data, including images, videos, texts, and speech datasets. This position is ideal for those who have a keen eye for detail and a commitment to precision.     Key Responsibilities:       Inputting and updating data into our database systems with high accuracy.         Verifying data by comparing it to source documents.         Reviewing data for deficiencies or errors, correcting any incompatibilities, and checking the output.         Complying with data integrity and security policies.         Ensuring the smooth and efficient processing of large volumes of data.         Collaborating with other teams to gather and organize data.         Meeting daily and weekly data entry targets and deadlines.       Qualifications:       High school diploma; further education or certification is a plus.         Proven experience as a Data Entry Operator or similar position.         Excellent typing skills with attention to detail and accuracy.         Familiarity with MS Office, data programs, and administrative duties.         Basic understanding of databases.         Good command of English, both oral and written.         Strong organizational and time management skills.       Benefits:       Opportunity to work in an innovative AI technology environment.         Exposure to diverse and cutting-edge data collection methods.         A supportive team that fosters learning and growth.         Competitive salary and benefits package.         Career advancement opportunities in a rapidly growing company.
column11: Administration, Time management, Diversity and Inclusion, Artificial Intelligence, Data collection, Office administration, data integrity, Technology solutions, MS Office, Data Entry Operator
